66
00:05:37,966 --> 00:05:40,166
That kiss was just roleplay.

67
00:05:40,866 --> 00:05:41,866
But now—

68
00:05:41,866 --> 00:05:44,033
I want a real one.

69
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,466
Hey—

70
00:05:47,466 --> 00:05:49,166
We’ve got to pack tonight.

71
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:50,466
We’re flying back tomorrow.

72
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,466
- No! You’re not going anywhere! Come here!
- Hey—!

73
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:55,333
- Rin, let go!
- hehe!

74
00:05:55,366 --> 00:05:57,066
Rin, the beer’s gonna spill!

75
00:05:57,066 --> 00:06:00,500
What are you doing, you crazy pup—Rin!

76
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:04,100
It’s spilling—stop, stop! That’s enough!

77
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:11,100
What are you doing?!

78
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,800
Rin!

79
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,733
Ugh, people are watching!

80
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:38,333
[MUSIC]

81
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:42,266
♪ Just by having you by my side today ♪

82
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:44,800
♪ Everything feels right ♪

83
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:49,833
♪ Listen to my heart — it whispers only your name.♪

84
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:53,733
♪ There’s no reason why I love you ♪

85
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:56,133
♪ It just has to be you ♪

86
00:06:56,466 --> 00:07:01,666
♪ The one I choose today… is you ♪

87
00:07:02,233 --> 00:07:07,433
♪ I want you here by my side. ♪

88
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:12,066
♪ Always. ♪ [Music]

89
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,400
Rin.

90
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,600
I’m here!

91
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,333
Breakfast’s ready.

92
00:07:26,966 --> 00:07:30,100
Look, I brought you some souvenirs!

93
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,133
- Ooh, you got sweets?
- And this one!

94
00:07:32,466 --> 00:07:35,100
And this— a special gift just for you, P’Prim.

95
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,833
- Custom-made from Kitakyushu!
- Aww!

96
00:07:38,866 --> 00:07:40,566
One of a kind—made by me.

97
00:07:40,566 --> 00:07:42,400
That’s so cute!

98
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,466
Oh!

99
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:45,733
How is it?

100
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,433
Thank you!

101
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,400
You're so adorable.

102
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,933
So, how was—

103
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:55,933
your Japan trip? Fun?

104
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:57,133
So much fun!

105
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:59,266
I got to do a lot of research too.

106
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:01,066
The weather was perfect, and the food—amazing.

107
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:04,833
- Sounds dreamy!
- I wanna go too.

108
00:08:05,566 --> 00:08:07,300
But still—nothing beats Thai basil stir-fry!

109
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,500
True that, I’ve never even been there!

110
00:08:11,033 --> 00:08:12,133
So…

111
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:15,133
How are things with Khun Aokbab? Getting along better?

112
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:20,800
Well—

113
00:08:20,966 --> 00:08:22,600
It’s good. Everything’s smooth.

114
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,066
Hmm.

115
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:27,066
Ever since you started working with her—

116
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,033
you’ve really changed, you know?

117
00:08:30,766 --> 00:08:32,833
Changed? I’m the same as always.

118
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,500
Maybe, but—

119
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:37,000
I can see you’re a lot happier.

120
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,233
And more thoughtful about others, too.

121
00:08:39,233 --> 00:08:40,733
You’re exaggerating.

122
00:08:42,266 --> 00:08:44,166
You’ve never bought me a gift before, have you?

123
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:47,200
See?

124
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,133
Really? Never?

125
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,000
Nope, never.

126
00:08:51,266 --> 00:08:53,800
Totally surprised—but hey,

127
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,800
thank you.

128
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,366
Uh—

129
00:08:57,366 --> 00:08:59,033
Can I ask you something?

130
00:08:59,066 --> 00:09:00,266
- About what?
- Hmm...

131
00:09:02,466 --> 00:09:04,600
- Let’s say, hypothetically, hypothetically!—
- Okay.

132
00:09:04,766 --> 00:09:07,800
If I like someone,

133
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:11,733
but I don’t know if they feel the same,

134
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:16,700
is there a way to tell what they think?

135
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,400
Well…

136
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:24,400
It’s simple.

137
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,600
If you care about them,

138
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:30,600
and they care about you too—

139
00:09:33,066 --> 00:09:34,966
that means—

140
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,233
wow.

141
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,266
That’s it?

142
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:44,700
Yep.

143
00:10:13,566 --> 00:10:14,833
Here!

144
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,333
Here it goes!

145
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:19,300
Eat up.

146
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:25,066
Hey, I think I’ll use some gimmicks—

147
00:10:25,066 --> 00:10:28,400
inspired by the places Khun Rain and Khun Ming visited—

148
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,866
and blend them into the design.

149
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:34,400
I want that feeling to stay in their home when they’re together.

150
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,266
What do you think?

151
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:38,400
- I like it.
- Sounds good. What else did you bring back from the trip?

152
00:10:39,466 --> 00:10:41,666
I feel like…

153
00:10:42,466 --> 00:10:45,400
I need to pay more attention to what’s around me.

154
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,666
All this time,

155
00:10:48,966 --> 00:10:50,900
I think I’ve overlooked something important.

156
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,866
The heart was right in front of me, but I couldn’t see it.

157
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:05,200
Are you talking about work—

158
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:06,800
or something else?

159
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,933
Work, obviously. What else would I mean?

160
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:15,433
Ever since you came back from Japan—

161
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,133
you’ve seemed different.

162
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:18,100
Hm.

163
00:11:18,366 --> 00:11:20,633
You never talk about work during meals.

164
00:11:20,766 --> 00:11:21,566
True.

165
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:22,933
Yeah!

166
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:25,000
if we wait till after, we’ll starve.

167
00:11:27,166 --> 00:11:29,733
- So are you and Rin still going to stay at Khun Rain’s house?
- Yeah.

168
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:32,633
Probably for a little longer.

169
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:35,966
Until the design feels just right.

170
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:42,166
And that’s the only reason you’re staying? Work?

171
00:11:42,366 --> 00:11:44,066
Or is there… something else?

172
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,266
Oh crap.

173
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,933
Khun Rain’s throwing a birthday party for Khun Ming.

174
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,266
He invited us. You coming?

175
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,500
Uh… not really my thing. You guys go ahead.

176
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,400
Where should we meet tomorrow, Sis?

177
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,100
[Sighs]

178
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,933
Chan! Chan!

179
00:12:29,966 --> 00:12:32,466
- Huh?
- Hmm, the pork’s kinda sweet today, right?

180
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:34,000
Sweet pork? What?

181
00:12:35,566 --> 00:12:37,733
Hey, we picked that out precisely, okay?

182
00:12:37,866 --> 00:12:38,700
It’s food wasted, you know.

183
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:41,266
- Yeah...yeah.
- Even the mushrooms taste sweet.

184
00:12:43,133 --> 00:12:47,033
- Hey, stop it!
- It’s pork tongue. We should stop teasing her, man. Let stop teasing her!

185
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,900
Did you get home yet, Sis?

186
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,166
I’ve finished packing.

187
00:13:11,033 --> 00:13:12,033
I’m so excited.

188
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,333
Good night.

189
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:24,100
I think I need to start paying more attention to the things around me.

190
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,466
All this time—

191
00:13:25,466 --> 00:13:28,966
I’ve overlooked something… even though the heart was right in front of me.

192
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,533
But I just couldn’t see it.

193
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:32,766
Ever since you came back from Japan—

194
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:34,533
you’ve really changed.

195
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:43,966
[Music] ♪ Love — I don’t know when it began, but it’s already here. ♪

196
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:48,766
♪ I don’t really understand why… but it had to be you. ♪

197
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:55,266
♪ I don’t know why — just seeing your smile feels like a beautiful painting. ♪

198
00:13:55,266 --> 00:13:59,766
♪ Like colors filling my heart with clarity. ♪

199
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:03,566
♪ We might not always fit perfectly, ♪

200
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:06,800
♪ But still, I just want to stay close to you. ♪

201
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:11,733
♪ You feel the same way, don’t you? ♪

202
00:14:11,766 --> 00:14:17,833
♪ Just having you by my side makes everything perfect today. ♪

203
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:23,300
♪ Listen to your heart — you’ll hear the answer is you (the answer is you). ♪

204
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:29,800
♪ There’s no reason for love, only that it has to be you. ♪

205
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:35,666
♪ The one I choose today is you. ♪

206
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:40,500
♪ I want you right here beside me. ♪

207
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:45,566
♪ Always. ♪ [Music]

208
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,166
We don’t have much time left at Khun Rain’s house.

209
00:14:58,466 --> 00:14:59,866
We’d better hurry up and finish the project.

210
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:06,266
And if we can’t finish in time?

211
00:15:06,266 --> 00:15:08,566
Where should we continue?

212
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:11,800
- Your place?
- My place.

213
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:19,966
Okay, and...

214
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,500
what if it gets late?

215
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,666
- Sleep in your...
- You can sleep in my room.

216
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:30,600
- Whoa!
- Watch out!

217
00:15:34,733 --> 00:15:35,900
Are you okay?

218
00:15:40,866 --> 00:15:43,100
Your hand…

219
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,700
Ah…

220
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,766
Sorry—

221
00:15:51,066 --> 00:15:52,400
I didn’t mean to!

222
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:57,533
It’s okay.

223
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,566
I’m totally fine.

224
00:15:59,766 --> 00:16:01,166
Fine about what?

225
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,400
Just… fine with everything.

226
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:16,700
Really. Don’t worry.

227
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:21,500
Okay?

228
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:23,600
Yeah.

229
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:43,133
What are you doing?

230
00:16:59,366 --> 00:17:00,633
Isn’t that Khun Rain’s house?

231
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:01,666
Yeah.

232
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:14,400
What do you think if I stay at the office for a while?

233
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,366
Why would you do that?

234
00:17:22,266 --> 00:17:23,933
I don’t think I can work properly.

235
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,400
I’m uneasy about this Khun Rain project.

236
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,100
You know our companies are rivals.

237
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,233
You don’t trust me, do you?

238
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,233
It’s not that—I just feel…

239
00:17:34,266 --> 00:17:35,500
If we had our own house—

240
00:17:36,133 --> 00:17:37,900
we’d each have our own workspace.

241
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:39,866
And we wouldn’t have to keep doubting each other like this.

242
00:17:41,566 --> 00:17:42,866
But we don’t, Tis.

243
00:18:00,366 --> 00:18:01,800
I’m sorry.

244
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:17,766
Please don’t be mad at me.

245
00:18:59,066 --> 00:19:00,500
Still mad at me?

246
00:19:02,466 --> 00:19:03,466
I’m not anymore.

247
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,733
What are you doing?

248
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:13,000
Hold still—don’t move or you’ll mess it up.

249
00:19:23,433 --> 00:19:24,366
There, looks good.

250
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:29,633
I’m heading out.

251
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:32,800
Drive safely, and—

252
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,666
don’t stress too much about the house.

253
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:36,400
Okay.

254
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,166
Go on, get to work.

255
00:19:39,066 --> 00:19:40,400
Love you.

256
00:19:48,866 --> 00:19:50,066
Bye-bye.

257
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:08,866
Ugh, call center again—so persistent.

258
00:20:10,966 --> 00:20:11,766
Hello?

259
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,700
You scammers who feeding off people’s misery.

260
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:16,133
You’re Khun Pad’s secretary, right, Khun Tertis?

261
00:20:16,566 --> 00:20:18,466
Wow, you even know my job title now?

262
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:22,333
Of course. We’ve met quite a few times already.

263
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:29,866
Who is this?

264
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,700
This is Thee from Mind Space.

265
00:20:33,366 --> 00:20:35,533
I just wanted to invite you out for lunch.

266
00:20:37,133 --> 00:20:38,966
