267
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:41,933
It might just help you and Khun Vee—

268
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,366
afford the house of your dreams.

269
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:05,666
Coffee’s here, my love.

270
00:21:08,666 --> 00:21:09,833
Careful, it’s hot.

271
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,666
Thanks.

272
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:21,700
Hey, sis—

273
00:21:21,966 --> 00:21:24,233
I’ve been thinking about Khun Rain’s house.

274
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:27,533
What if we use Japanese home-building techniques?

275
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,900
And for the interior, add some Kitakyushu vibes.

276
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,333
I think Khun Rain and Khun Ming would love it.

277
00:21:35,166 --> 00:21:36,466
I was thinking the same thing.

278
00:21:38,266 --> 00:21:39,133
Really?

279
00:21:39,466 --> 00:21:41,033
We are in sync, right?

280
00:22:10,666 --> 00:22:11,733
What are you looking at?

281
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:17,433
Nothing. I wasn’t looking.

282
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,733
You feeling okay?

283
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:22,000
- You’ve got a fever? Let me check—
- Eh—

284
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,366
Eh— no, I’m fine.

285
00:22:25,766 --> 00:22:27,533
It’s just the weather.

286
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:29,933
You look flushed though.

287
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:32,300
It’s hot!

288
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:39,633
Hmm.

289
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:40,700
Hey, sis—

290
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:43,133
We’ve been to Japan together for days.

291
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:44,366
So,

292
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:47,033
We’re pretty close already, right?

293
00:22:48,066 --> 00:22:49,066
I guess so.

294
00:22:51,266 --> 00:22:52,466
So, um—

295
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:56,433
the guest room ceiling is leaking.

296
00:22:56,866 --> 00:22:58,500
Still not fixed.

297
00:22:58,633 --> 00:23:01,033
Can I sleep in your room tonight?

298
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,700
The guest room

299
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,266
It’s leaking,

300
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,100
Uh-huh.

301
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,533
And when we sleep—

302
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,366
can I cuddle you?

303
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,366
What kind of question is that?

304
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:29,566
Are you crazy?

305
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:31,100
What? You’re so silly.

306
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:34,233
Where are you going? That’s mine!

307
00:23:34,633 --> 00:23:35,500
Sorry!

308
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:38,866
You didn’t say no, so I’ll take that as a yes.

309
00:23:54,866 --> 00:23:56,466
- Hello.
- Hi there.

310
00:23:56,666 --> 00:23:58,166
Oh, thank you.

311
00:23:58,300 --> 00:23:59,166
Hello.

312
00:23:59,366 --> 00:24:00,566
Please, make yourself comfortable.

313
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:03,033
Hello, Khun Ming. Happy birthday.

314
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:04,366
Thank you so much.

315
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:05,333
Thanks again.

316
00:24:05,366 --> 00:24:06,433
That’s so sweet of you.

317
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,866
Hello, Khun Rain, Khun Ming.

318
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:08,833
Hi there.

319
00:24:08,866 --> 00:24:09,933
Happy birthday.

320
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:12,166
I carefully picked this birthday gift—

321
00:24:12,166 --> 00:24:13,533
especially for you, Khun Ming.

322
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,800
Thank you, that’s so lovely.

323
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:18,200
About the house renovation design—

324
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:20,900
Is there any particular feature you’d like?

325
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:24,133
Or any details you’d like us to finalize, please let us know.

326
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:25,500
- Sure.
- Of course.

327
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,400
You really take good care of the clients, don’t you, Khun Thee?

328
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,533
Hello there.

329
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,066
- Hello.
- Hi.

330
00:24:33,566 --> 00:24:35,966
Oh, you both came too, Khun Chan, Khun Pad?

331
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:38,566
Of course, we had to be here.

332
00:24:38,733 --> 00:24:39,900
Why wouldn’t we?

333
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:54,200
Hey, guys! Check this out —

334
00:24:54,333 --> 00:24:55,900
I’ve got something to show you!

335
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:56,700
What is it?

336
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:57,700
Whoa.

337
00:24:57,766 --> 00:25:00,566
- It’s our company sign!
- Whoa!

338
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,900
Damn, that looks great.

339
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:04,933
Sammitr Co. (Three Brotherhood Co.) is gonna be huge, I’m telling you.

340
00:25:04,966 --> 00:25:07,666
- Yeah.
- We’ll make it together. Our future’s bright.

341
00:25:07,666 --> 00:25:09,666
Here, grab your glasses! Hold them up!

342
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:13,733
Let’s drink to this — we’ll never betray or abandon each other.

343
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:18,966
- I’m counting on you, seniors!
- Cheers!

344
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:21,600
What the hell did you do, Thee?!

345
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:24,766
- How could you make a deal behind our backs?!
- Why didn’t you tell us first?!

346
00:25:25,266 --> 00:25:27,766
I already talked to the client! What was I supposed to do?

347
00:25:27,966 --> 00:25:30,866
You know damn well that budget isn’t enough to finish the project.

348
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,700
I’ve already taken it.

349
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,233
You just have to make it work.

350
00:25:34,566 --> 00:25:36,466
How can you be so damn irresponsible?

351
00:25:38,866 --> 00:25:40,400
You’re always bragging about—

352
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:41,300
How good you are

353
00:25:41,666 --> 00:25:43,166
prove it like you said!

354
00:25:43,566 --> 00:25:45,533
What the hell are you saying, man?!

355
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,900
Hey, what are you doing?!

356
00:25:48,066 --> 00:25:49,966
If you’re gonna keep deciding everything on your own,

357
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,166
We’re done. We quit.

358
00:25:51,266 --> 00:25:52,866
Hey, you can’t just walk away like that!

359
00:25:52,966 --> 00:25:54,533
- I already accepted the job!
- Enough!

360
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:56,000
What a stupid decision, man.

361
00:25:56,066 --> 00:25:57,266
- I don’t want to work with you anymore.
- Where are you going?!

362
00:25:57,300 --> 00:25:58,600
I’m out. Let go of me.

363
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,000
I already accepted... Fuck whatever!

364
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:04,733
Go ahead, just leave!

365
00:26:04,833 --> 00:26:06,433
Just leave! All of you!

366
00:26:06,466 --> 00:26:09,566
Fine! I’ll do it myself! Don’t come crawling back!

367
00:26:33,833 --> 00:26:34,966
I told you, didn’t I?

368
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:36,566
It was never going to work.

369
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,366
No wonder they dropped the deal.

370
00:26:40,566 --> 00:26:42,366
If you came here just to talk shit,

371
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:43,600
then get lost.

372
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:46,433
You’ve got some nerve, huh?

373
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:47,900
We quit—

374
00:26:48,100 --> 00:26:49,733
and now you still took our project to finish it yourself.

375
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,200
What did you expect me to do?!

376
00:26:51,633 --> 00:26:53,700
The company was falling apart after you left!

377
00:26:53,933 --> 00:26:56,233
I did everything I could to keep it alive!

378
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,400
Tell me—

379
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,600
where was I wrong?!

380
00:27:00,333 --> 00:27:02,000
- You bastard!
- Chan!

381
00:27:03,833 --> 00:27:05,200
You hit my brother, huh?!

382
00:27:06,233 --> 00:27:07,033
- Shit—

383
00:27:07,533 --> 00:27:09,733
- Chan! What the hell are you doing?!

384
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:15,800
- You want some?!

385
00:27:15,800 --> 00:27:17,333
- Stop it! Enough!

386
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,200
You wanna hit me, you asshole?!

387
00:27:27,233 --> 00:27:29,566
- You—
- Shit!

388
00:27:29,566 --> 00:27:32,566
- Chan, that’s enough! I said stop, Chan!

389
00:27:33,466 --> 00:27:35,033
- Stop! Stop!

390
00:27:35,033 --> 00:27:38,000
- You think you’re tough, huh?!
- Damn it!

391
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,566
- Stop! Both of you!

392
00:27:43,633 --> 00:27:45,133
I said stop!

393
00:27:45,166 --> 00:27:48,166
- You—
- That’s enough!

394
00:27:52,933 --> 00:27:54,933
Stop it, both of you!

395
00:28:05,133 --> 00:28:06,500
Have you been here long?

396
00:28:07,866 --> 00:28:09,300
We just got here, actually.

397
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:10,766
Perfect timing, too.

398
00:28:11,366 --> 00:28:12,866
Oh—here, this is for you, Khun Ming.

399
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:14,566
- Thank you.
- Wishing you lots of happiness.

400
00:28:14,966 --> 00:28:17,100
Just having you here makes me happy already. Thank you so much.

401
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:18,466
- It’s my pleasure.

402
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,566
The dessert’s here!

403
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:36,900
Thanks.

404
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:39,100
[Sigh]

405
00:28:39,466 --> 00:28:40,733
it’s just work.

406
00:28:42,166 --> 00:28:43,600
Kidding.

407
00:28:45,666 --> 00:28:47,766
If you’re gonna bring up what happened earlier,

408
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:48,800
I’m not answering.

409
00:29:00,433 --> 00:29:02,833
P'Prim said I should get the HPV vaccine—

410
00:29:02,966 --> 00:29:04,433
Cervical cancer prevention.

411
00:29:04,933 --> 00:29:06,866
Come with me, please? I’m scared of needles.

412
00:29:07,100 --> 00:29:09,133
Or… we could go together!

413
00:29:09,900 --> 00:29:11,900
Eh—no way, I’m not going.

414
00:29:11,933 --> 00:29:13,966
Are you trying to jinx me or what?

415
00:29:14,266 --> 00:29:15,533
I’m not!

416
00:29:15,533 --> 00:29:18,533
I’m just worried about you.
I want us to stay together for a long time.

417
00:29:21,566 --> 00:29:22,500
So…

418
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:24,866
about that cuddling—

419
00:29:26,766 --> 00:29:27,833
Answer, hurry!

420
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:31,633
No answer means permission granted,

421
00:29:34,933 --> 00:29:35,866
Okay

422
00:29:44,466 --> 00:29:45,966
Hold on, I’ve got to take this call.

423
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:01,766
Hey, Stop calling me.

424
00:30:01,966 --> 00:30:04,300
We’re not in a position to be talking like this.

425
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:05,733
You’re not coming to the party?

426
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,400
Didn’t you get what I said?

427
00:30:10,866 --> 00:30:12,033
Stop calling me.

428
00:30:17,066 --> 00:30:18,233
Why can’t I call you?

429
00:30:19,566 --> 00:30:21,400
We haven’t even broken up yet.

430
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:32,466
I still want to talk to you.

431
00:30:54,233 --> 00:30:56,600
I’m looking forward to seeing your work.

432
00:30:56,633 --> 00:30:58,933
You all seem very dedicated.

433
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:01,966
Yes, especially since Khun Rin and Khun Aokbab

434
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,333
even moved into the house themselves.

435
00:31:04,333 --> 00:31:06,666
I’m excited and can’t wait to see the design.

436
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:07,566
Yes.

437
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:11,533
How long have they been there?

438
00:31:12,566 --> 00:31:14,166
For a little while now.

439
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:16,066
Please, make yourselves at home.

440
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:19,533
Hello. Thank you so much for coming.

441
00:31:37,100 --> 00:31:38,500
When do we have to pay them?

442
00:31:44,733 --> 00:31:46,100
I’ll take care of it right away.

443
00:31:46,433 --> 00:31:48,033
Okay.

444
00:31:57,100 --> 00:31:58,333
What’s up? Something wrong?

445
00:32:09,066 --> 00:32:10,033
What’s the matter, hmm?

446
00:32:12,733 --> 00:32:14,400
You know you can always talk to me, right?

447
00:32:19,066 --> 00:32:20,166
I…

448
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:25,666
It’s just…

449
00:32:31,766 --> 00:32:33,533
We shouldn’t keep secrets from each other.

450
00:32:36,166 --> 00:32:37,666
I have a proposal for you.

451
00:32:38,033 --> 00:32:39,800
It might let you and Vee—

452
00:32:40,066 --> 00:32:41,833
Finally buy your dream home.

453
00:33:01,700 --> 00:33:02,600
What is it?

454
00:33:04,633 --> 00:33:05,533
Are you okay?

455
00:33:10,500 --> 00:33:11,433
Nothing.

456
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:13,766
Can you make me some porridge? I’m hungry.

457
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,033
Now?

458
00:33:16,566 --> 00:33:18,100
Please… make it for me.

459
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:26,833
This house has so many little corners.

460
00:33:26,833 --> 00:33:29,633
It makes cleaning really difficult.

461
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,566
Even with housekeepers, I doubt they can get every spot.

462
00:33:34,233 --> 00:33:35,066
This one—

463
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,200
The kitchen.

464
00:33:36,466 --> 00:33:37,466
I think...

465
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:41,033
We should have a center island like this.

466
00:33:41,300 --> 00:33:44,666
Move the range hood to the center.

467
00:33:44,900 --> 00:33:46,133
So when they cook—

468
00:33:46,266 --> 00:33:48,533
Khun Ming can reach everything easily.

469
00:33:49,266 --> 00:33:50,166
Like this.

470
00:33:52,766 --> 00:33:53,866
What do you think?

471
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,266
Mmm, that’s nice.

472
00:34:05,366 --> 00:34:07,366
When they’re cooking together—

473
00:34:07,666 --> 00:34:09,700
They can do it like this too.

474
00:34:50,066 --> 00:34:51,000
What are you doing here?

475
00:34:54,166 --> 00:34:55,300
I’m going to stay here.

476
00:34:58,033 --> 00:34:58,833
No way.

477
00:34:59,766 --> 00:35:01,400
You’re not welcome here.

478
00:35:02,666 --> 00:35:04,266
If you have the right to stay in this house—

479
00:35:04,466 --> 00:35:05,666
then so do I.

480
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,300
I already asked Khun Rain for permission.

481
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:17,733
This house has quite a few damaged areas, doesn’t it?

482
00:35:18,033 --> 00:35:21,100
Just from the outside, I can already see leaks and water damage.

483
00:35:22,166 --> 00:35:23,666
I bet there are more inside.

484
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,400
Have you checked them yet?

485
00:35:31,266 --> 00:35:32,133
Already did.

486
00:35:32,333 --> 00:35:34,833
Every bedroom’s leaking right now.

487
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,966
There’s no room left for anyone else.

488
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:39,000
Then I’ll just sleep with Aokbab.

489
00:35:39,433 --> 00:35:42,066
We used to share a room all the time when we traveled together.

490
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:47,200
Unfortunately, P'Aokbab’s room isn’t available right now.

491
00:35:47,266 --> 00:35:48,833
Because I’m sleeping next to her.

492
00:35:48,966 --> 00:35:50,466
We even cuddle when we sleep.

493
00:35:53,966 --> 00:35:56,866
I think once you’ve finished your inspection, you should head back.

494
00:35:57,233 --> 00:35:58,833
I’m staying overnight.

495
00:35:59,366 --> 00:36:00,766
I can sleep on the sofa.

496
00:36:02,300 --> 00:36:04,800
Fine, do whatever you want.

497
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:06,333
Aokbab—

498
00:36:06,533 --> 00:36:08,500
Show me around the house.

499
00:36:15,166 --> 00:36:16,233
I’ll take you.

500
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:18,100
I’ll show you every single corner.

501
00:36:18,200 --> 00:36:19,733
How’s that sound, Auntie Mind?

502
00:36:20,233 --> 00:36:20,766
Let’s go.

503
00:36:30,966 --> 00:36:32,333
After you, Auntie.

504
00:37:00,066 --> 00:37:02,466
I know what you're trying to do.

505
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,733
But let me tell you—it’s not going to work.

506
00:37:08,300 --> 00:37:09,666
I’m just here to work.

507
00:37:10,100 --> 00:37:11,633
I want everything to be fair.

508
00:37:12,033 --> 00:37:12,866
That’s all.

509
00:37:14,333 --> 00:37:15,400
Fair?

510
00:37:17,133 --> 00:37:18,066
You mean, farewell?

511
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:23,433
The only thing P'Aokbab still has for you—

512
00:37:24,766 --> 00:37:26,233
is hatred. Nothing else.

513
00:37:26,766 --> 00:37:27,733
You should know that.

514
00:37:28,700 --> 00:37:30,000
And you think she loves you?

515
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,866
I know Aokbab very well.

516
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,766
She’s someone who—

517
00:37:44,966 --> 00:37:47,200
Always knows what she likes and doesn’t like.

518
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:49,166
If she hesitates—

519
00:37:49,766 --> 00:37:51,366
it means she doesn’t like you.

520
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,100
No matter how hard you try to care about her—

521
00:37:59,500 --> 00:38:01,200
she doesn’t like younger people.

522
00:38:45,966 --> 00:38:47,966
Do you want shrimp, sis? I’ll peel it for you.

523
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:49,966
Mhm.

524
00:38:57,833 --> 00:39:00,733
Crab from the same place we used to go to.

525
00:39:01,033 --> 00:39:02,233
I’ll peel it for you.

526
00:39:10,566 --> 00:39:12,800
Try it, see if it still tastes the same.

527
00:39:20,266 --> 00:39:21,200
Sis—

528
00:39:21,500 --> 00:39:23,800
Have this shrimp instead — I peeled it for you.

529
00:39:23,833 --> 00:39:26,000
Shrimp’s better anyway.

530
00:39:26,900 --> 00:39:28,566
Aokbab likes crab.

531
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:30,233
Not always.

532
00:39:30,366 --> 00:39:33,966
Maybe she doesn’t like the same old things anymore.

533
00:39:34,166 --> 00:39:35,966
New things might only taste good the first time.

534
00:39:36,100 --> 00:39:37,566
- And how would you know?
- Rin.

535
00:39:39,433 --> 00:39:40,466
If you’re done eating—

